  <TD width=655 align='left' height= 1215 ><font size= 2  face= Verdana Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif >First
    of all a Big Shout out to Brell Serilis and perhaps the dumbest Fuck to ever
    log into EQ, Morsereg. Read about 8 pages, gonna wait for the Movie to get
    the rest.</font>
    <p><font size= 2  face= Verdana Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif >Back
    to Vex Thal finally ! Since we rotate stuff here on Povar like good little
    civilized Norrathians we cleared Vex Thal version 2.0 for the first time
    last week, and wow what can i say somethings haven't changed at all...</font>
    </p>
    <p><b><font arial, helvetica, sans-serif face= Verdana  size= 4 >What
    [Feign Death]?</font></b></p>
    <p><font face= Verdana  size= 2 ><img border= 0  src= images/news/18September02/lotsofmobs.jpg  width= 693  height= 627 ></font></p>
    <p><font face= Verdana  size= 2 ><img border= 0  src= images/news/18September02/lotsofmobs2.jpg  width= 746  height= 630 ></font></p>
    <p align= left ><font face= Verdana  size= 2 >For the most part the loot changes that have been added or
    updated seem to be finally done right, theres obviously a few things that
    slipped through the cracks...like this little coveted <a href= images/news/18September02/skyorb.jpg >Orb</a>
    . </font></p>
    <table border= 0  width= 87%  height= 307 >
      <tr>
        <td width= 22%  height= 301 ><img border= 0  src= images/news/18September02/atencorpse.jpg  width= 105  height= 217 ></td>
        <td width= 78%  height= 301 ><font face= Verdana  size= 2 >Loot off of Aten was very nice, including
          Ancient Spell for Nuvian, Neck for Kastrina, Arms for Bentos, Orb for
          Zaar, and Breastplate of Judgement for Gaven</font></td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <p align= left ><font face= Verdana  size= 2 >Also with addition of loot to 'trash mobs' it makes what
    would normally be hours upon hours of mindless clearing, a <b>NON-STOP
    FUCKING LOOT FEST. </b>Entirely too much loot to list so just showing
    corpses:</font></p>
    <p align= left ><font face= Verdana  size= 2 ><img border= 0  src= images/news/18September02/corpses.jpg  width= 720  height= 252 ></font></p>
    <p align= left ><font face= Verdana  size= 2 ><Edit: Other corpses removed to save webspace></font></p>
    <p align= center > </p>
    <p align= left ><font face= Verdana  size= 2 >Other fun loots included: Kast on Cloak of Black Wind, Faldy
    on C3 wand, Gruffy/Elvaar on Thorny Chain Sleeves, Rombus on some gay book
    on a stick, Bentos on Ring of the Crimson Bull, Athlene on new Panties (old
    ones had worn out from overuse), Minael on Cloak of Frozen Flame, and other
    people got stuff too...thats what I wrote down and remembered. OH, and
    Irontaail got a ...VEIL ..OMG ...8)</font></p>
    <p align= left ><font face= Verdana  size= 2 >Also off'd Cursed, got two Books and Render of Souls - Grats
    Zagore, Eylia, and Clara. High priest put out some gay druid thing for
    Archie, no fucking idea what it was...but he seemed excited. Xerath got
    Halo, and Munwin got priest shoulder thingy. </font></p>
    <p align= left ><font face= Verdana  size= 2 >Oh and Finally....</font></p>
    <p align= center ><b><font face= Verdana  size= 3 >WHY GOD WHY AM I STILL DOING EXPERIENCE
    IN FUCKING OLD SEBILIS?</font></b></p>
    <p align= left ><font face= Verdana  size= 2 >Fungus Grove was the new exp spot for level
    60ish people with the release of Luclin, it got nerfed, unnerfed, renerfed,
    nerfed with a twist, and now I have no idea what its current status is -
    cause I hate that fucking zone. Velious had Velketor's lab which also has
    been nerfed, unnerfed, and renerfed sideways. Basically anytime people in EQ
    find a new good spot to get experience (i.e. Shadowhaven guards, Dawnshroud
    level 60's) Verant just nerfs them so no one in their right mind would want
    to kill them. They could however realize that these too could be a viable
    alternative to traditional exp zones and simply adjust the encounter to have
    better risk versus reward. Instead its much easier to give Shadowhaven
    guards 300K HPs so no one would ever think of killing them, and change Level
    60 con mobs in DS to light Blue con mobs...BUT LEAVE THEM THE SAME, so they
    are still just as hard to kill but like 15 levels lower. </font></p>
    <p align= left ><font face= Verdana  size= 2 >So instead of there being multiple zones to
    get exp in, we are forced to stay in Sebilis, Velks, FG maybe, and Deep/Akheva/ME.
    ME brings new meaning to the word 'suck' , Akheva has limited spots to keep
    a group at, and The Deep should have a way higher zone experience modifier.
    Anyways, back to Sebilis~  </font></p>
